    • Method Detail

      • getTerm

        public Term getTerm(java.lang.String termQuery)
        Get a complete Term object from Entrez Gene. If the database already contains the top match, then it will be the source for the Term. In the case that multiple entities have the same name, all of their relationships will be put into the same 'composite' Term object. Caution: may not return exact match to query. Search is based on Entrez Gene native search, try it here: http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene
        Specified by:
        getTerm in interface ResourceWrapper
        Parameters:
        termQuery - String to query for
        Returns:
        Term object that was the top result from Entrez Gene, or composite from db

      • getTerm

        public Term getTerm(java.lang.String termQuery,
                    boolean exact)
        Similar to getTerm(String), but with option to enforce exact matching to the termQuery String. Returns null when there is no exact match.
        Parameters:
        termQuery - String to query for
        exact - boolean to enforce exact matching to termQuery
        Returns:
        match Term object, or null

      • getTerms

        public java.util.Collection<Term> getTerms(java.lang.String termQuery,
                                           int amountRequested)
        Find a list of Term objects corresponding to the termQuery, limited by amountRequested. Will never return a list larger than amountRequested, but may return a smaller list. Order of the list is the relevance ranking from Entrez Gene search. Database cache is used to retrieve terms whenever possible; when the database does NOT contain the required information, the Entrez Gene web service is queried instead.
        Specified by:
        getTerms in interface ResourceWrapper
        Parameters:
        termQuery - String to query for
        amountRequested - Maximum number of results to attempt to find
        Returns:
        ArrayList of Terms, size is never greater than amountRequested
